messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 4/21/00 4:20:41 AM, Unschooling-dotcom@egroups.com writes:

<< I only feel like I have a lot of catching up to do as an adult
because there are a lot of things I have an interest in that I wish I
already knew (e.g. Latin & piano) - and that I could have learned back
then if I'd known how to be diligent. >>

this is the case with many of us adults! home/unschooled or not... many
teens arent in a place to be diligent bc they are busy growing, sleeping,
eating, being. if it had been forced upon you then, w/out your pro-activity,
you may have rejected it anyway...
erin
